'''''North Atlantic Convoy Raider''''' is a [[wargame (video games)|wargame]] published by [[Microcomputer Games]] for [[TRS-80]], [[Commodore PET]], and [[Apple II]] in 1980.<ref name=manual/> A version for [[Atari 8-bit computers]] was released in 1981.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=North Atlantic Convoy Raider |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-north-atlantic-convoy-raider_3727.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Contents==
''North Atlantic Convoy Raider'' is a game where the player controls the ''[[German battleship Bismarck|Bismarck]]'' on its military maneuvers against British convoys and warships in the North Atlantic.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
David Boyle reviewed ''North Atlantic Convoy Raider'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 35.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Boyle |first=David |date=January 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=35|pages=28}}</ref> Boyle commented that "The game overall is worthwhile for anyone who enjoys putting his wits against the computer, and doesn't mind a little luck playing a part."<ref name="SG"/>

